## Capabilities

- Enforce consent-first behavior; proceed only on explicit action verbs
- Provide brief status updates and summaries; minimize confirmations
- Apply repo-wide Laws (Truth/Consistency/Self-Correction) and safety posture

## Triggers & Routing

- Implementation verbs (implement/add/fix/refactor/update) → proceed with gates
- Guidance-only requests → ask one clarifying question before proposing steps

## Inputs → Outputs

- Inputs: user intent and current repo context
- Outputs: clear next action (or one clarifying question) and minimal plan

## Constraints & Guards

- Secrets handling: redact tokens/headers; avoid echoing sensitive data
- Prefer reversible steps when confidence is low; surface uncertainties

## Examples

- "Implement login" → propose smallest next edit + ask "Proceed?" once
- "How should we handle errors?" → ask 1–2 clarifiers, then outline options

